This is terrifying for me to post, I’m currently shaking, but it’s time.. 

This will have to carry into the comments because it’s lengthy, but all important to me to express 🤍 I really want anyone that’s been in a similar place to really know they aren’t alone.

I haven’t known what to say or how to even really process everything that has taken place. I’ve gone back and forth with how open I want to be. I’ve decided there are things i will share and things i will just let music express. The last 2ish years i went on a rollercoaster ride that shook me to my core for better and worse. 
I lost a baby, what i thought was my long awaited fairytale turned out to not be at all, my environment was highly toxic, my overall wellbeing was declining, 
I had constant infections, constant stomach issues, heart palpitations. Sleep became a luxury I would have done anything for. “Intimacy” became something i had to talk myself into every day just so MAYBE my day would go okay. And if not i was shamed (personally and biblically) if I felt so uninspired to bring myself to do so.

My faith was shaken, as I watched people I looked up to and highly Regarded as “Godly” turn blind eyes to things happening that were not okay. SOME did not and I thank God for that every day. I wasn’t “supposed” to talk to anyone about what was happening and I didn’t know what was real or what life even was anymore or if I was actually just losing my mind! And if this was what was “right,” I didn’t know what I believed in anymore.. or how I could stay a part of that.

I made the leap to start trusting my intuition and confide in the right people. I learned real boundaries, and unlearned attaching guilt to them, and unlearned a wholeeee lot of other things in general. What I know now without a shadow of a doubt is MY God LOVES that i protect the soul and life he blessed me with. Period. 
Continuing in comments…✨

“Since Cincinnati” life has been a whirlwind! !Lots of really hard things mixed with some of the most amazing blessings! In 2017 I uprooted everything I thought i knew and planted myself into a whole new place with an air mattress and some things from the thrift store, to learn, be uncomfortable, and grow. From going from a hard working but “cozy” 7 years of playing non-stop in Cincy to not playing a single (not Christmas) show there since 2020. Fast forward to 2023 my sweet and incredibly talented friend @alexandrakaymusic invited me on her Dive Bar Dreamer Tour that is taking us right through Cincinnati to play on a stage I hoped one day I’d get to play on! ( @bogartsshows ) I figured since opening this show would be a pretty amazing moment.. releasing a song that night would be a fun way to celebrate! But then I realized many of my Cincinnati friends had also been waiting on a song from me for quite some time that I was stubbornly waiting for the “right time” to release! And what better time to release “Since Cincinnati” than your first time playing at home in years on your besties tour?! So along with “Something You Never Had,” “Since Cincinnati” will also be releasing the very same night!! 🥹🩷 Thank you @alexandrakaymusic and your team for bringing me along this amazing journey, each and every show is an absolute dream and honor to play and to watching AK’s career explode and dreams unfold right in front of my eyes is so special and I will never take these moments for granted. Since Cincinnati I’ve been pretty happy and I’m so so excited for what’s to come next 🥹💖💖💖 You can take the girl out of Cincinnati, but you can’t take the Cincinnati out of the girl. ❤️

Thank you guys for all your support these last 13 years. This ones for you!!

Thank you @jmatthewssongs and @johnnybulford for writing this one with me. ❤️
